{
  "video_id": "RlLrvnnTDDU",
  "title": "Pathophysiology - Type II diabetes | Endocrine system diseases | NCLEX-RN | Khan Academy",
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 2060.0,
      "end_time": 5020.0,
      "text": "- Diabetes Mellitus is\na group of disorders"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 5020.0,
      "end_time": 8421.0,
      "text": "that's caused by improper\nfunction of insulin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 8421.0,
      "end_time": 11852.0,
      "text": "which is a hormone\nproduced by the pancreas."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 12276.0,
      "end_time": 15875.0,
      "text": "And insulin is responsible\nfor helping regulate"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15875.0,
      "end_time": 19695.0,
      "text": "blood sugar, or glucose\nlevels, in the blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 19695.0,
      "end_time": 22156.0,
      "text": "Now since it's a group of diseases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 22156.0,
      "end_time": 24594.0,
      "text": "there are actually multiple\ndifferent underlying causes"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 24594.0,
      "end_time": 26254.0,
      "text": "of diabetes mellitus."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 26254.0,
      "end_time": 30463.0,
      "text": "And one of these causes is\nknown as Type 2 Diabetes."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 30978.0,
      "end_time": 33672.0,
      "text": "Now, before we dive into the actual cause"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 33672.0,
      "end_time": 37074.0,
      "text": "of Type 2 Diabetes, let's first\nget a better understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 37074.0,
      "end_time": 39623.0,
      "text": "of how exactly insulin works."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 39720.0,
      "end_time": 41608.0,
      "text": "And there are two major steps."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41718.0,
      "end_time": 44713.0,
      "text": "So, imagine that you just ate a big meal."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 44713.0,
      "end_time": 47441.0,
      "text": "Maybe like a bowl of pasta or something."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 47441.0,
      "end_time": 50936.0,
      "text": "And your body is currently\nabsorbing all of those nutrients"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 50936.0,
      "end_time": 54790.0,
      "text": "from your digestive system\ninto your bloodstream."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 54790.0,
      "end_time": 57877.0,
      "text": "Now one of these nutrients is glucose,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 57877.0,
      "end_time": 60339.0,
      "text": "and as your body absorbs it, that glucose"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 60339.0,
      "end_time": 63422.0,
      "text": "starts building up in the blood stream."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 63671.0,
      "end_time": 67177.0,
      "text": "And in this feeding or absorptive state,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 67177.0,
      "end_time": 70990.0,
      "text": "your body wants to store\nthis glucose in places like"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 70990.0,
      "end_time": 75452.0,
      "text": "the liver and muscle cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 76372.0,
      "end_time": 79018.0,
      "text": "so that it can be used for energy later"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 79018.0,
      "end_time": 80876.0,
      "text": "when the body needs it."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80876.0,
      "end_time": 83732.0,
      "text": "But unfortunately, glucose on its own"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 83732.0,
      "end_time": 85950.0,
      "text": "can't get into these cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 85950.0,
      "end_time": 89044.0,
      "text": "In a sense, these cells are locked."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 89351.0,
      "end_time": 91592.0,
      "text": "But fortunately, the pancreas"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 91592.0,
      "end_time": 93518.0,
      "text": "is able to help with this problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 93518.0,
      "end_time": 95167.0,
      "text": "So there are a couple types of cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 95167.0,
      "end_time": 99416.0,
      "text": "in the pancreas that\nsense blood sugar levels."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 99416.0,
      "end_time": 103323.0,
      "text": "And these cells are located\nin the islets of Langerhans."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 104176.0,
      "end_time": 107532.0,
      "text": "And these green cells here\nin the islets of Langerhans"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 107532.0,
      "end_time": 110492.0,
      "text": "are meant to represent the Beta cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 110492.0,
      "end_time": 113952.0,
      "text": "And when the blood glucose increases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 113952.0,
      "end_time": 117214.0,
      "text": "the Beta cells of the\npancreas sense this change,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 117214.0,
      "end_time": 121289.0,
      "text": "and they secrete a\nhormone known as insulin"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 121289.0,
      "end_time": 122288.0,
      "text": "into the blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 122288.0,
      "end_time": 125690.0,
      "text": "And what insulin does\nis it acts like a key"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 125690.0,
      "end_time": 129544.0,
      "text": "that can unlock these\ncells so that the glucose"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 129544.00000000001,
      "end_time": 133753.0,
      "text": "can be stored in both the\nliver and the muscle cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 133840.0,
      "end_time": 135605.0,
      "text": "So you can see that there are two steps"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 135605.0,
      "end_time": 138309.0,
      "text": "in order for insulin to function properly."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 138309.0,
      "end_time": 141363.0,
      "text": "And the first is that these Beta cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 141363.0,
      "end_time": 144126.0,
      "text": "of the endocrine portion of the pancreas"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 144126.0,
      "end_time": 146574.0,
      "text": "have to be functioning in order to"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 146574.0,
      "end_time": 148908.0,
      "text": "secrete the insulin into the blood."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 148908.0,
      "end_time": 153720.0,
      "text": "And then second, these cells\nhave to respond to the insulin"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 153772.0,
      "end_time": 156825.0,
      "text": "in order to unlock them\nso that the glucose can be"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 156825.0,
      "end_time": 161783.0,
      "text": "taken out of the blood to\ndecrease the blood glucose levels."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 161783.0,
      "end_time": 164488.0,
      "text": "Now, diabetes mellitus can be caused"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 164488.0,
      "end_time": 167982.0,
      "text": "by dysfunction at either\nof these two steps."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 167982.0,
      "end_time": 171465.0,
      "text": "So if the Beta cells\naren't functioning properly"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171465.0,
      "end_time": 175447.0,
      "text": "or they're being destroyed,\nsuch as in Type 1 Diabetes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 175447.0,
      "end_time": 177502.0,
      "text": "there isn't enough insulin to be produced"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 177502.0,
      "end_time": 179266.0,
      "text": "to unlock the cells."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 179266.0,
      "end_time": 181611.0,
      "text": "And what happens is that the glucose"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 181611.0,
      "end_time": 183271.0,
      "text": "builds up in the bloodstream,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 183271.0,
      "end_time": 186766.0,
      "text": "and that person will\ndevelop diabetes mellitus."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 186766.0,
      "end_time": 188949.0,
      "text": "However, similarly in step two,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 188949.0,
      "end_time": 191468.0,
      "text": "if the cells aren't properly responding"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 191468.0,
      "end_time": 195485.0,
      "text": "to the insulin in the blood,\nthen they can't be unlocked."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 195485.0,
      "end_time": 197807.0,
      "text": "And the glucose will build\nup in the blood vessels"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 197807.0,
      "end_time": 199246.0,
      "text": "and you'll get hyperglycemia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 199246.0,
      "end_time": 201522.0,
      "text": "and the person will\ndevelop diabetes mellitus."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 201522.0,
      "end_time": 203808.0,
      "text": "So this is what I meant\nearlier when I said"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 203808.0,
      "end_time": 205945.0,
      "text": "that diabetes is a group of disorders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 205945.0,
      "end_time": 207930.0,
      "text": "because multiple different mechanisms"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 207930.0,
      "end_time": 210264.0,
      "text": "can result in diabetes mellitus."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 210264.0,
      "end_time": 213886.0,
      "text": "So, in general, Type 2 Diabetes is caused"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 213886.0,
      "end_time": 216509.0,
      "text": "by dysfunction of this second step."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 216509.0,
      "end_time": 219923.0,
      "text": "And this is known as insulin resistance."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 219923.0,
      "end_time": 224265.0,
      "text": "So, in Type 2 Diabetes, the\nBeta cells of the pancreas"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 224265.0,
      "end_time": 226287.0,
      "text": "are functioning properly, and they're able"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226287.0,
      "end_time": 229721.0,
      "text": "to produce insulin, but\nthat insulin isn't able"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 229721.0,
      "end_time": 233930.0,
      "text": "to have its proper effect on\nthe cells throughout the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 233947.0,
      "end_time": 235548.0,
      "text": "However, it is important to note"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 235548.0,
      "end_time": 237383.0,
      "text": "that as the disease does progress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 237383.0,
      "end_time": 239147.0,
      "text": "the pancreas can become effective"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 239147.0,
      "end_time": 241748.0,
      "text": "and eventually decrease\nits insulin production."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 241748.0,
      "end_time": 243583.0,
      "text": "But in general, Type 2 Diabetes"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 243583.0,
      "end_time": 247901.0,
      "text": "is thought of as primarily due\nto this insulin resistance."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 247901.0,
      "end_time": 249921.0,
      "text": "So what exactly causes the cells"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 249921.0,
      "end_time": 252684.0,
      "text": "to become resistant to insulin?"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 252684.0,
      "end_time": 255308.0,
      "text": "Well, unfortunately there's\nno simple answer to this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 255308.0,
      "end_time": 258141.0,
      "text": "and the cause of Type 2\nDiabetes is very complex"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 258141.00000000003,
      "end_time": 259998.00000000003,
      "text": "and includes many different factors"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 259998.0,
      "end_time": 262518.0,
      "text": "that work together to cause the problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 262518.0,
      "end_time": 264525.0,
      "text": "So let's get a little\nbit better idea of this."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 264525.0,
      "end_time": 266546.0,
      "text": "I'm gonna just erase\nsome of our work here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 266546.0,
      "end_time": 269042.0,
      "text": "so we can get a little more room."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 269042.0,
      "end_time": 271108.0,
      "text": "So what are some of these risk factors?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 271108.0,
      "end_time": 272780.0,
      "text": "Well one of the most important ones"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 272780.0,
      "end_time": 274545.0,
      "text": "is actually genetics."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 274545.0,
      "end_time": 276519.0,
      "text": "In fact, having a family history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 276519.0,
      "end_time": 278840.0,
      "text": "say in someone's parents or grandparents,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 278840.0,
      "end_time": 282323.0,
      "text": "of Type 2 Diabetes is one\nof the biggest risk factors"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 282323.0,
      "end_time": 284901.0,
      "text": "for developing Type 2 Diabetes."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 284901.0,
      "end_time": 287187.0,
      "text": "Other factors include obesity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 287187.0,
      "end_time": 291292.0,
      "text": "hypertension, and increasing age."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 292157.0,
      "end_time": 295303.0,
      "text": "And it's the interaction of\nall these different factors"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 295303.0,
      "end_time": 300175.0,
      "text": "plus more that end up resulting\nin insulin resistance."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 300445.0,
      "end_time": 303185.0,
      "text": "But how can we maybe understand\nthis a little bit better?"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 303185.0,
      "end_time": 305822.0,
      "text": "Well, one of the factors\nthat we understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 305822.0,
      "end_time": 308086.0,
      "text": "maybe a little bit better\nthan some of the others"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 308086.0,
      "end_time": 310024.0,
      "text": "is the effect of obesity."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 310024.0,
      "end_time": 312648.0,
      "text": "So let's bring back that\nlock I described earlier."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 312648.0,
      "end_time": 314947.0,
      "text": "So if you think of obesity as kind of"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 314947.0,
      "end_time": 317861.0,
      "text": "this perpetual feeding\nstate, or in a sense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 317861.0,
      "end_time": 322319.0,
      "text": "that the body is\ncontinuously being exposed"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 322319.0,
      "end_time": 323352.0,
      "text": "to insulin released by the pancreas"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 323352.0,
      "end_time": 325871.0,
      "text": "in an effort to bring\ndown the increased glucose"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 325871.0,
      "end_time": 328274.0,
      "text": "from this perpetual feeding state."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 328274.0,
      "end_time": 331595.0,
      "text": "Over time, the receptors on\nthe cells, or these locks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 331595.0,
      "end_time": 334961.0,
      "text": "become desensitized to the insulin."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 334961.0,
      "end_time": 337376.0,
      "text": "And they become resistant to its effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 337376.0,
      "end_time": 339373.0,
      "text": "So let's use an analogy to help understand"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 339373.0,
      "end_time": 342078.0,
      "text": "this idea of resistance."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 342078.0,
      "end_time": 346617.0,
      "text": "So instead of a lock,\npretend this is a person."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 346617.0,
      "end_time": 351024.0,
      "text": "And this person decides\nto put on a baseball cap."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 351179.0,
      "end_time": 353432.0,
      "text": "So when you first put on a baseball cap,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 353432.0,
      "end_time": 355011.0,
      "text": "you can feel it on your head,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 355011.0,
      "end_time": 358076.0,
      "text": "however, over time, say 10, 15 minutes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 358076.0,
      "end_time": 361315.0,
      "text": "this constant stimulation\nof the touch receptors"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 361315.0,
      "end_time": 365552.0,
      "text": "results in a desensitization\nto the feeling of the ball cap"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 365552.0,
      "end_time": 370173.0,
      "text": "on your head, and it feels\nlike it's no longer there."
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 370173.0,
      "end_time": 373324.0,
      "text": "So this is kind of similar\nto the cells in the body."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 373324.0,
      "end_time": 375808.0,
      "text": "If they're constantly\nexposed to this insulin,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 375808.0,
      "end_time": 377770.0,
      "text": "they'll stop responding to it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 377770.0,
      "end_time": 380289.0,
      "text": "and the cell won't become unlocked."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 380289.0,
      "end_time": 382170.0,
      "text": "Now initially the pancreas is able"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 382170.0,
      "end_time": 386025.0,
      "text": "to compensate for this resistance\nby producing more insulin."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 386025.0,
      "end_time": 388381.0,
      "text": "However, eventually as time progresses,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 388381.0,
      "end_time": 389821.0,
      "text": "the pancreas cannot keep up"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 389821.0,
      "end_time": 391783.0,
      "text": "to overcome the insulin resistance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 391783.0,
      "end_time": 394151.0,
      "text": "and eventually the body\nwill lose its ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 394151.0,
      "end_time": 396821.0,
      "text": "to lower the blood glucose\nlevel with insulin."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 396821.0,
      "end_time": 399445.0,
      "text": "And this will result in hyperglycemia"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 399445.0,
      "end_time": 402742.0,
      "text": "and the complications that\nare associated with it."
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 402742.0,
      "end_time": 405110.0,
      "text": "But this process can take time."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 405110.0,
      "end_time": 408222.0,
      "text": "In fact, from the time this\ninsulin resistance starts"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 408222.0,
      "end_time": 411647.0,
      "text": "to when someone would develop\nsymptoms of Type 2 Diabetes"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 411647.0,
      "end_time": 414584.0,
      "text": "can actually take multiple years."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 414584.0,
      "end_time": 416941.0,
      "text": "But at the same time, early\ndiagnosis and treatment"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 416941.0,
      "end_time": 419668.0,
      "text": "is critical to prevent\nthe serious complications"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 419668.0,
      "end_time": 421688.0,
      "text": "associated with diabetes."
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 421688.0,
      "end_time": 424440.0,
      "text": "And for this reason, it's very important"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 424440.0,
      "end_time": 426542.0,
      "text": "to screen people who are at risk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 426542.0,
      "end_time": 429618.0,
      "text": "people who have some\nof these risk factors."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 429618.0,
      "end_time": 432021.0,
      "text": "It's important to screen\nthem for Type 2 Diabetes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 432021.0,
      "end_time": 434680.0,
      "text": "so they should regularly have\ntheir blood glucose levels"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 434680.0,
      "end_time": 436723.0,
      "text": "monitored for hyperglycemia,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 436723.0,
      "end_time": 439881.0,
      "text": "so that it can be detected\nand treatment can be started"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 439881.0,
      "end_time": 443282.0,
      "text": "even before he or she\nwill develop symptoms."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 443282.0,
      "end_time": 445105.0,
      "text": "So I hope this gives you\na better understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 445105.0,
      "end_time": 447845.0,
      "text": "of what causes Type 2 Diabetes."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 447845.0,
      "end_time": 452408.0,
      "text": "It's not caused by a problem\nwith the pancreas itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 452408.0,
      "end_time": 455074.0,
      "text": "and the ability to produce insulin."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 455074.0,
      "end_time": 459068.0,
      "text": "Instead, it's caused by\nthis insulin resistance,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 459068.0,
      "end_time": 460356.0,
      "text": "by the cells throughout the body"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 460356.0,
      "end_time": 463122.0,
      "text": "that are supposed to respond to insulin."
    }
  ]
}